<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="135">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="135" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="135">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,311,443]" pageId="29" pageNumber="135">
We failed to collect any specimens of this species during this study and our attempts to access the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,312,338]" pageId="29" pageNumber="135">type</typeStatus>
material were not fruitful. Based on its diagnostic characters, original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Stackelberg A. A." box="[1180,1390,346,372]" pageId="29" pageNumber="135" pagination="426 - 439" refId="ref19034" refString="Stackelberg A. A. 1949. New data on the genus Eumerus Mg. (Diptera, Syrphidae) of the Palaearctic fauna. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 30 (3 - 4): 426 - 439." type="journal article" year="1949">Stackelberg 1949</bibRefCitation>
) and the identification key (
<bibRefCitation author="Stackelberg A. A." box="[497,705,381,408]" pageId="29" pageNumber="135" pagination="18 - 229" refId="ref19072" refString="Stackelberg A. A. 1961. Palaearctic species of the genus Eumerus Mg. (Diptera, Syrphidae). Trudy Vsesoyuznogo Entomologicheskogo Obshchestva 48: 18 - 229." type="journal article" year="1961">Stackelberg 1961</bibRefCitation>
), this species is readily separated from other Iranian species studied through this research.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
